social_posts.post_text: Wind blown sands…. This is one of the most beautiful patterns I’ve seen formed along the beaches of Oregon…. Massive expanse of black sand creates beautiful patterns in the fine red sand and evening light
A winter meal with a Dark Eyed Junco
Crisp mornings and chirping friends. (Dark Eyed Junco)

Snowy flight …
This weekend I was pretty certain I was not going to be able to photograph these impressive birds. But I’m definitely glad I stuck through the sleet and snow and gave it a try anyway
The award for the cutest of the falcon family goes to…… this cute little American kestrel… smallest falcon of North America
Time for a middle of the road nap
Electric skies… this past trip to Iceland was a memorable one, during my first evening I was greeted with these electric skies

Frozen sunrise  An Incredible morning adventure to these falls... two stuck super jeeps... white out conditions with 40mph+ winds.. Polar Stratospheric clouds... and beautiful blue waters... what a great memory

Depth... my talk tomorrow for Out of Chicago Live will be all about creating Depth and and Dimension, with Dodging and burning and other photoshop techniques..... here is one of the images I will be post processing

Happy 3 year wedding anniversary to us!! 

Marrying @nickpagephotography was my best choice in lifetimes. Pappa Bear has seen me when my soul was at its ugliest, and still chose to love me. He is my tether to reality when the world gets tumultuous, and I love him for his whispered witty comments and no nonsense vibe. 9 years of adoring this fella has changed me for the better.

Happy wedding anniversary my Love. I love you more than penguins and excellent lighting COMBINED!

Scroll for the craziest sky I have ever witnessed…. I’m not a spiritual person, but these Arora borealis shows connect with me in a deeper way then I knew was possible… just remembering what it was like to look upon these lights dancing across the sky raises the hair on my neck and gives me goosebumps
The fastest way to shoot a focus stacked, exposure blend.

Solitude…
After three days we finally found this beautiful snowy owl and were rewarded with observing it from a distance for a couple hours… rather than invading its space we kept our distance and respected its space… such a rewarding weekend
Aurora storm… currently working on the video from this amazing night, so many images and time lapse is to go through this when it’s going to be a good one
Tomorrow’s video shares probably the most incredible 24 hours of photography I have ever had….
Eruption. I will never tire of photographing the beautiful shapes and sculptures that an angry sea creates.
Forest hike. One of my favorite little streams to explore

Throwback to the best concert that I’ve ever been to….let alone got to photograph. The gentlemen of the road was a special thing to get to witness. In this photo Marcus Mumford fr m Mumford and Sons sings Broken Crown

Electric mountain…. This was a day to remember….. maybe it was the fact that it was @shainblumphotography s birthday…. Maybe it was the Mexican food guts… maybe it was the crazy storms overhead….. but I will never forget this epic night!
The lone tree gets all the attention… it’s totally OK to be different
Incredibly happy with how this one turned out. Because people will ask, I went through HD aluminum  based in Vancouver Washington
Looking back on this epic night. It’s not every day you get to witness Aurora like this from south eastern Washington state.
Aurora farms…. Pretty awesome when you witness this from the palouse.
Can you imagine if all businesses operated like airlines?
I think I am the first photographer to ever shoot this unknown, unnamed waterfall :-) some places are popular for a reason. Such a beautiful waterfall.
Stormy sunsets are my favorite sunsets

The rolling hills of home. 
Swipe to see the rest of the scene

Layers of light …
Sunlit foliage, reflecting off a mountain stream
Today be thankful for the country we are lucky enough to argue over…. Choose people over politics…. Love thy neighbor…. And put others first.
The deadline for the give away is August 1st! I will be randomly selecting the winners on the morning of August 1st and announcing them here!

Thunder on the farmstead…
This is the shoe to where a storm formed behind myself, and @shainblumphotography and struck the ground less than a quarter mile away behind us…. Needless to say, that was the end of the shoot :-)
Last week I had the pleasure of camping at this beautiful location listening to these beautiful falls all night. The original White, noise app!

Goodbye, Iceland….
Flying home today after 16 days and perhaps my favorite country in the world. I love this place for the common sense, pragmatic, open minded humanitarian culture… not to mention the epic vistas and raw natural places. Definitely not looking forward to going home to hot temperatures, smoke filled skies, and the divided angry American culture. The more I travel, the less I relate with American culture. There are truly beautiful people and places out there.

Best campsite ever…
Can you believe that this is the mountain we saw every morning when we opened our tent? Camping in the highlands of Iceland is officially my new favorite experience.
There are a few things I enjoy more than watching the sky dance
Lonely mountain. Currently putting together this week’s video. Really excited to be able to share some of my Icelandic adventure with all of you.
I’m really excited about this coming Sunday’s YouTube video. Such a awesome adventure and I’m excited to share it with everyone…. Here’s the first image I capture in the video.

Into the valley of fire… today’s YouTube video is one that I’m proud of. If you have a moment to check it out, you will notice that I referred to this area of Iceland as Mordor. Mordor was most certainly what I was thinking about when I was looking at the scene, it’s also the inspiration for how I decided to post process it. Who knew that Mordor could be so beautiful.

Just getting back from Utah where I was teaching at the Out of Moab Conference.  It was my first opportunity photographing the beautiful Arches National park under a night sky.  This is a two image blend... both images taken a a couple minutes apart. 
Sky shot at f2.8 Iso 6400 for 20 seconds.. 
the foreground shot at f2.8, ISO 1600 for 2.5 Minutes. 
Photoshop makes these two image blends so easy, one of the many things Lightroom cant do.

This past week I got to experience the beauty that is the Dingle Peninsula. My good friend. @peter_gordon_art chauffeured me around the peninsula and on this evening we watched the sunset over the Atlantic.
Who will be out chasing the eclipse this week? Here is my shot from 2017
Shoreline storm… so excited to be headed back to the coast!
My group had an awesome time yesterday exploring the back roads and looking for fall color. The Pacific Northwest is beautiful when the oranges and yellows complement the Mossey greens.
Last week we had beautiful light on the Oregon coast. I love the moments after a storm passes, as the sun peaks underneath the rain clouds.
I photographed this beautiful Merlin during my last trip to Iceland…. What a beautiful bird
Golden hour over the wizards hat
Man I miss the magical coastlines of Kauai. I hate that views like this are fenced off during big surf due to the negligence of the ignorant and ill advised.
